Diana Ionescu (born 1981 in Câmpina, Romania) is a Romanian pianist and First Prize Winner of the prestigious George Enescu International Piano Competition, in its 2001 Edition.
She then entered Dan Grigore’s class at Bucharest’s National Music University, from which she graduated in 2003.
